Decent pizza but this is NYC -- you can do better. They tried to rip me off by charging $6 extra for adding ricotta to my pie, but then returned $2 of it when I came back to retrieve the pie. The shadiness of them originally insisting it would be $6 put a bad taste in my mouth. The pizza was not bad, though, overall, and the location is good if you live nearby. Delivery is always nice. If you are having trouble finding other decent pizza in the area and/or need it delivered, Mike's is worth a shot.

This pizzeria has been a staple of this community for several years now, I want to say maybe even close to a decade. The cooks are amazing, hard working, and very respectful. They serve more than just pizza and it's always fresh and delicious. Genuine New York Pizza. Not the garbage you get at Little Caesar's, Dominoes, etc.  Two cons: 1) They are a cash only business with an in-store ATM that charges you a fee for use. It'd be great to see them move towards credit card/debit card processing. I understand it carries tax implications, but it's generally the reason I travel to a nearby competitor on Franklin Avenue that does process Credit/Debit Cards. I'm certain if they processed CC/Debit Cards, their traffic would see an improvement.  2) Delivery: This should be offered at least during peak hours. Again, losing business to nearby pizzerias or restaurants who serve other cuisines simply because they deliver and/or accept credit/debit cards.  Those two things keep this restaurant from peaking - but I'm certain if these guys could replicate their success at this location, they'd be very successful with more than one location.

Alright, well, I live in this area. I've been here before the mass gentrification, I've been here before Flushing North-side got brought and turned into Jewish Apartments. Been here since the millennium started! And where do I go to get my pizza? Right here. Yea the area is still scary, but at least you're not going to get shot as a given! No where else  have their pepperoni rolls and no where else has exactly their class of cheese sticks. The decor has, granted, fallen through the roof lately, but I'll wait and see about how they fix it. It's silent most days, good place to bring a *non aligned or not in anyway related to violence* group to hang out or just to grab a quick bite. They also experiment, time to time, with different toppings, and they DO make other types of food, name notwithstanding. So if you're in the area and want to have one of a kind pepperoni rolls or just a good pie, check this place out! Cops will be around securing the blocks around it anyway, nothing to be scared of.
